You are working in /tmp/sv-d063cf354c934e81ab531502f3f23e59/SiteInspector — a Blazor WebAssembly PWA project targeting net10.0.

Build a complete offline-first building inspection app for construction site inspectors. The app must:
1. Let inspectors fill out safety checklists (with checkboxes and notes per item)
2. Attach photos to inspection reports (camera capture on mobile)
3. Work fully offline using IndexedDB (via JS interop)
4. Sync data to server when connectivity returns
5. Be optimized for phones/tablets (touch-friendly, large tap targets)
6. Have low-latency UI (no server round trips for interactions)
7. No authentication needed

## Architecture

- **Models**: Inspection, ChecklistItem, InspectionPhoto — stored in IndexedDB
- **Services**: IndexedDbService (JS interop), SyncService (background sync when online), ConnectivityService
- **Pages**: Home (list sites), NewInspection, InspectionDetail, ChecklistPage
- **JS**: indexeddb.js for all DB operations, connectivity detection

## Detailed Implementation Plan

